<ext_description linkend="General_model_parameter_arm.General_model_parameter">
<p>An <b>General_model_parameter</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="independent_property:arm:Independent_property_arm.Independent_property"/>
that is a named input/output of a model used in the definition of the interface,
in the sense of exposed method of communicating with the model, to the model which is or may be provided with
or result in an actual value when the model is used or invoked. The model to which the <b>General_model_parameter</b>
is related can be of any type.</p>
<example>A UML 2 Behavior State Machine is an example of a model.</example>
<p>An instance of <b>General_model_parameter</b> may be classified using 
<express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:arm:Classification_assignment_arm.Classification_assignment"/>
to specify its direction. Four directions are defined in Annex F.
The default direction, should it not be classified is, ParameterDirection-in.</p>
<note>See Annex F for an example ISO 10303-21 file showing a classified <b>General_model_parameter</b>.</note>
<p>The default value for the parameter may be specified using 
<express_ref linkend="independent_property_representation:arm:Independent_property_representation_arm.Independent_property_representation"/>.
</p>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="General_model_parameter_arm.Parameter_value_representation_item">
<p>A <b>Parameter_value_representation_item</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/>
that adds to the set of items used to represent the value of a <express_ref linkend="general_model_parameter:arm:General_model_parameter_arm.General_model_parameter" />.
It is not a restriction that a <express_ref linkend="general_model_parameter:arm:General_model_parameter_arm.General_model_parameter"/>
may only be represented using a <b>Parameter_value_representation_item</b>.
</p>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="General_model_parameter_arm.Parameter_value_representation_item.parameter_value">
the value of the parameter
</ext_description>
